set(auto).

# Predicates:
Monkeypox(x) ::: x is Monkeypox.
InfectiousDisease(x) ::: x is an infectious disease.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
MonkeypoxVirus(x) ::: x is the monkeypox virus.
OccurIn(x, y) ::: x can occur in y.
Animal(x) ::: x is an animal.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
SymptomOf(x, y) ::: x is a symptom of y.
Fever(x) ::: x is a fever.
Headache(x) ::: x is a headache.
MusclePains(x) ::: x is muscle pains.
FeelingTired(x) ::: x is feeling tired.
Glu(x) ::: x is a glu.
Person(x) ::: x is a person.
FeelTiredWhen(x, y) ::: x feels tired when they get y.

# Premises:
# Monkeypox definition and causation
Monkeypox(mp)
InfectiousDisease(mp)
CausedBy(mp, mpv)
MonkeypoxVirus(mpv)

# Occurrence of Monkeypox virus
# The monkeypox virus can occur in humans.
∀x (Human(x) → OccursIn(mpv, x))

# Hierarchies of beings
# All humans are mammals.
∀x (Human(x) → Mammal(x))
# All mammals are animals.
∀x (Mammal(x) → Animal(x))
# All persons are humans.
∀x (Person(x) → Human(x))

# Specific symptoms of Monkeypox
# Fever is a symptom of Monkeypox.
SymptomOf(fever, mp)
# Headache is a symptom of Monkeypox.
SymptomOf(headache, mp)
# Muscle pains are a symptom of Monkeypox.
SymptomOf(musclePains, mp)
# Feeling tired is a symptom of Monkeypox.
SymptomOf(feelingTired, mp)

# Manifestation of Monkeypox symptoms in people
# If a person has Monkeypox, they experience its symptoms.
∀p (Person(p) ∧ HasDisease(p, mp) → SymptomOf(fever, mp) ∧ SymptomOf(headache, mp) ∧ SymptomOf(musclePains, mp) ∧ SymptomOf(feelingTired, mp))
# If a person has Monkeypox, they experience at least one of the specific symptoms.
∀p (Person(p) ∧ HasDisease(p, mp) → ExperiencesSymptom(p, fever) ∨ ExperiencesSymptom(p, headache) ∨ ExperiencesSymptom(p, musclePains) ∨ ExperiencesSymptom(p, feelingTired))

# Causation of feeling tired by Monkeypox symptoms
# If a person has Monkeypox, they will feel tired.
∀p (Person(p) ∧ HasDisease(p, mp) → ExperiencesSymptom(p, feelingTired))

# Causation of feeling tired by a glu
# People feel tired when they get a glu.
∀p (Person(p) ∧ Glu(g) ∧ Gets(p, g) → ExperiencesSymptom(p, feelingTired))

# Conclusion:
¬∃x (Human(x) ∧ Glu(x))

# Conclusion:
¬∃x (Human(x) ∧ Glu(x))
